{
    "problem": "Let $r$ be a root of $x^2 + 5x + 7 = 0.$  Compute\n\\[(r - 1)(r + 2)(r + 6)(r + 3).\\]",
    "level": "Level 4",
    "type": "Intermediate Algebra",
    "solution": "Since $r$ is a root of $x^2 + 5x + 7 = 0,$ $r^2 + 5r + 7 = 0.$\n\nWe have that\n\\begin{align*}\n(r - 1)(r + 2)(r + 6)(r + 3) &= (r - 1)(r + 6)(r + 2)(r + 3) \\\\\n&= (r^2 + 5r - 6)(r^2 + 5r + 6) \\\\\n&= (-13)(-1) = \\boxed{13}.\n\\end{align*}"
}